## 3. src/canvas/CommitmentMap.css

Styles for the commitment map canvas:

- .commitment-map: width 100%, height 100%, min-height 600px, position relative, overflow auto, background var(--bg)
- .commitment-map__header: padding, font-size 16px, font-weight 600, border-bottom, shows the goal text
- .commitment-map__canvas: position relative, min-width and min-height based on grid size, padding 40px
- .commitment-map__bg: absolute fill, pointer-events none. Draw subtle grid dots using radial-gradient (small dots at intersections). Draw a diagonal guide line using a repeating-linear-gradient at 45deg (very faint, like rgba(88,166,255,0.06))
- .commitment-map__axis-label: very subtle axis labels. X='Progress →' at top, Y='Commitment ↓' at left. Font-size 11px, text-muted color, opacity 0.5
- Card positioning class: .map-card { position: absolute; transition: all 0.2s ease; }

The overall feel should be dark, minimal, like a mission planning surface — not a colorful automation builder.

